WEBVTT

00:04.371 --> 00:06.373
[ Man ]
One, two! One, two, three!

00:32.533 --> 00:36.804
In what has become a winter
tradition, members of the
Zarlon Seven Polar Bear Club...

00:36.904 --> 00:40.039
today took the plunge
into a river of liquid ammonia.

00:40.140 --> 00:42.542
[ Cheering ]

00:43.877 --> 00:45.813
There were no survivors.

00:45.912 --> 00:49.048
[ Laughs ]
Takes all kinds.

00:49.149 --> 00:51.719
And now with
his annual Xmas message,

00:51.819 --> 00:54.322
here's the head of
the Xmas Safety Council,

00:54.421 --> 00:56.323
the head of Walter Cronkite.

00:56.423 --> 00:59.159
Season's warnings,
Linda and Morbo.

00:59.259 --> 01:02.329
This guy's too trustworthy.
What's his angle?

01:02.429 --> 01:06.167
In all the tinsel and terror
of the holiday season,

01:06.266 --> 01:09.602
we too often underestimate
that murderous brute...

01:09.703 --> 01:11.971
better known as Santa Claus.

01:12.072 --> 01:15.308
With images of last year's
Gingerbread Massacre...

01:15.409 --> 01:17.844
freshly baked
into our memories,

01:17.944 --> 01:21.349
I remind you
to bolt your doors,

01:21.448 --> 01:25.186
say good-bye to your pets
and lock your children
in the closet.

01:25.286 --> 01:29.289
This is Walter Cronkite
saying "I told you so."

01:29.390 --> 01:31.859
[ Hammering ]

01:33.194 --> 01:35.829
Sacred boar of Western
and Eastern Samoa,

01:35.929 --> 01:37.865
we got to secure
for Santa's arrival.

01:37.965 --> 01:41.634
[ Signal Pulsing ]
Just as well. I'm getting
tired of this wood show.

01:41.734 --> 01:43.971
[ All Grunting ]

01:44.070 --> 01:46.439
Cover that fireplace,
confound you!

01:46.539 --> 01:50.177
I've only a few years to live.
I don't want to spend them dead.

01:50.277 --> 01:52.846
We're pushing as hard
as we can.

01:52.945 --> 01:54.847
Oh, pushing!

01:54.948 --> 01:56.849
Aah! Oh!

01:56.950 --> 02:00.188
Oh, we're doomed!
Every year we're doomed.

02:00.287 --> 02:04.391
Thanks be I had these
bulletproof shutters installed.
[ Beeping ]

02:08.195 --> 02:10.663
Whoa! Aah!

02:11.831 --> 02:13.734
** [ "Deck The Halls" ]

02:13.834 --> 02:18.338
Bring it on, Santa!
That bloodthirsty cadaver
junkie can't touch us...

02:18.438 --> 02:21.341
as long as we're
not stupid enough
to leave this building.

02:21.442 --> 02:23.644
All right!
Uh-huh!

02:23.743 --> 02:27.814
In a related matter,
you'll be delivering this
sack of children's letters...

02:27.914 --> 02:31.651
directly to Santa at
his death fortress on Neptune.

02:35.155 --> 02:37.691
[ Engine Laboring ]

02:43.864 --> 02:47.033
These letters are
real butt nutters.
Listen to this one.

02:47.134 --> 02:51.372
-"Dear Santa--"
-[ Girl's Voice ] Please, please
don't bring me any gifts.

02:51.472 --> 02:54.508
The bicycle you fired
at me last year
from your bicycle gun...

02:54.608 --> 02:56.710
really tore up
my insides.

02:56.810 --> 03:00.514
Awful. Let's read some more.
"Dear Santa--"

03:00.614 --> 03:02.949
[ Boy's Voice ]
Please bring me
a coffin for Grandpa.

03:03.050 --> 03:05.453
You choked him with
a chestnut last year,

03:05.552 --> 03:09.689
and he's beginning
to smell a lot like Xmas,
if you know what I mean.

03:09.789 --> 03:11.692
[ Chair Creaking ]

03:11.792 --> 03:13.693
It's not fair!

03:13.794 --> 03:16.629
In my day, Xmas was supposed
to bring people together,
not blow them apart.

03:16.729 --> 03:19.233
Sure, but who's gonna do
anything about it?

03:19.332 --> 03:23.135
Certainly not us.
No, sir.
Certainly yes us. Uh-huh, sir.

03:23.236 --> 03:26.407
We've gotta bring back
the kind of Xmas I remember.

03:26.507 --> 03:31.044
Fry's right.
It's time to sit
on Santa's lap, and hard.

03:36.417 --> 03:40.086
[ Machine Gun Fire ]
[ Dog Barking ]

03:45.293 --> 03:49.062
Oh, look. A cute
little welcoming party.

03:50.897 --> 03:53.501
[ Coughing ]
Hey, wanna buy
a tiny little kidney?

03:53.600 --> 03:55.502
I'll let you punch me
for a buck.

03:55.603 --> 03:59.072
Look. We've got mail for Santa.
Are you his elves?

03:59.171 --> 04:01.140
We're not elves.
We're Neptunians.

04:01.241 --> 04:03.311
We're just shrimpy
because he doesn't feed us.

04:03.411 --> 04:06.447
You hit me.
You owe me a dollar.

04:06.546 --> 04:08.981
[ Dogs Growling ]
Aah! Aah!

04:09.081 --> 04:11.818
[ Grunting, Muttering ]

04:13.486 --> 04:15.455
Help. You got
any food?

04:15.556 --> 04:18.125
Old tea bags, chewed gum,
apple cores?

04:18.225 --> 04:20.127
Come on!
We're starving here!

04:20.226 --> 04:24.163
-But you live
in a gingerbread house.
-It's food or shelter, not both.

04:24.264 --> 04:28.035
You lazy runts.
Don't you get paid
for making the toys?

04:28.134 --> 04:30.870
- Who said "toys"?
- Toys? Someone said "toys"?

04:30.971 --> 04:32.872
False alarm, folks.

04:32.973 --> 04:36.310
There's no reason to make toys,
since Santa judges everyone
to be naughty.

04:38.446 --> 04:42.882
That's it. I'm gonna deliver
a gift of my boot up Santa's
chimney. Where is he?

04:42.983 --> 04:45.619
There, in his ice fortress.

04:48.187 --> 04:50.524
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

04:50.624 --> 04:53.225
We'll need help getting in.
Any volunteers?

04:57.297 --> 05:00.300
I'll help you.
Aw, phooey.

05:09.843 --> 05:13.480
** [ Barking "Jingle Bells" ]

05:15.716 --> 05:17.985
[ Squawks ]

05:19.319 --> 05:22.154
An omen?
Dinner.

05:22.254 --> 05:25.858
[ Thunderclap ]

05:25.959 --> 05:28.362
[ Sinister Laughter ]

05:28.461 --> 05:30.363
Let's see
who's been naughty...

05:30.463 --> 05:33.033
and who's been naughty.

05:33.132 --> 05:35.034
Oh! Oh! Oh!

05:35.134 --> 05:38.738
Mobsters beating up a shopkeeper
for protection money.

05:38.838 --> 05:40.941
Very naughty.

05:41.040 --> 05:45.045
[ Groaning ]
Shopkeepers not paying
their protection money.

05:45.144 --> 05:47.514
Exactly as naughty!

05:50.350 --> 05:52.284
I saw that!

05:52.386 --> 05:54.353
Huh?

05:54.454 --> 05:58.024
- We brought you mail.
- Don't you ever knock?

05:58.125 --> 06:01.228
Who knows what naughty things
I could be watching?

06:01.327 --> 06:04.764
- I get New Orleans
on this thing, you know.
- Don't kill us!

06:06.699 --> 06:09.702
Santa's a robot.
So we should be able
to destroy him...

06:09.802 --> 06:11.738
with a logical
paradox.

06:11.838 --> 06:13.973
Bender, you better
cover your ears.

06:15.475 --> 06:18.144
Holy night! Intruders!

06:19.312 --> 06:22.882
Hold it, Santa.
[ Humming ]

06:22.983 --> 06:26.819
Consider this:
You are programmed
to destroy the naughty.

06:26.920 --> 06:29.889
But many of those you destroy
are, in fact, nice.

06:29.990 --> 06:32.560
I submit to you
that you are naughty...

06:32.659 --> 06:35.394
and that, logically,
you must destroy yourself.

06:35.495 --> 06:38.932
[ Gibbering ]

06:40.332 --> 06:42.002
Yea!
[ Laughing ]
Yea!

06:43.302 --> 06:45.838
Nice try,
but my head was built...

06:45.939 --> 06:49.341
with paradox-absorbing
crumple zones.

06:49.442 --> 06:51.343
Aah!
Aah!

06:51.444 --> 06:53.980
[ Humming, Yelling ]

06:54.081 --> 06:56.249
[ All Screaming ]

07:02.689 --> 07:05.526
[ Beeping ]

07:05.625 --> 07:08.995
- [ Bender Yelling ]
- [ Screaming ]

07:11.798 --> 07:14.334
Wait. This is what
we're running from.

07:19.038 --> 07:21.007
Faster! Faster!

07:21.108 --> 07:23.511
Whoa! Oh!
Aah!

07:25.045 --> 07:28.314
Aah!
Aah!

07:28.415 --> 07:30.550
[ Screaming ]

07:31.819 --> 07:34.321
[ All Screaming ]

07:35.488 --> 07:37.725
[ Screaming Continues ]

07:37.824 --> 07:41.161
Oof!
[ Blubbering ]

07:41.261 --> 07:43.497
[ Engine Starting ]

07:43.596 --> 07:46.533
[ Rockets Firing ]
Why aren't we moving?

07:46.634 --> 07:51.004
I don't know.
Usually when I do stuff
like this, the ship moves.

07:54.173 --> 07:56.744
Ho, ho-- Huh?

08:02.081 --> 08:04.016
[ Grumbling ]

08:04.117 --> 08:06.353
[ Grunting ]

08:06.452 --> 08:09.055
He's trapped!
[ All ]
Hooray!

08:10.658 --> 08:15.495
- Now we can make toys again.
- [ All ] Toys! Toys! Toys!

08:15.596 --> 08:19.231
And I can deliver them.
Billions and billions
in one night.

08:19.331 --> 08:22.002
Ha! No human
could do all that.

08:22.101 --> 08:24.672
- Evel Knievel could.
- Nuh-uh!

08:24.771 --> 08:27.406
Santa's right.
We need some sort of robot.

08:29.742 --> 08:32.345
Aw, crap!
I'm some sort of robot.

08:33.713 --> 08:35.716
[ Neptunians ]
Hooray!

08:35.816 --> 08:37.684
Hooray!

08:37.784 --> 08:40.019
Hooray!
Ooh!

08:44.091 --> 08:46.025
Bender can't be Santa.

08:46.125 --> 08:49.395
He wasn't built to
Yuletide specifications.

08:49.495 --> 08:53.933
Oh, yeah? Well, I wasn't built
to steal Leela's purse either,
but that didn't stop me.

08:54.033 --> 08:57.971
Bender!
Bow before your new Santa!

08:58.071 --> 09:00.072
[ Neptunians ]
Our hero!

09:00.173 --> 09:02.542
[ Bells Jingling ]
* We are free
and fairly sober *

09:02.643 --> 09:04.543
* With so many toys
to build *

09:04.644 --> 09:06.947
* The machines
are kinda tricky *

09:07.047 --> 09:08.948
* Probably someone
will be killed *

09:09.048 --> 09:11.150
* But we gladly work
for nothing *

09:11.250 --> 09:14.988
* Which is good because
we don't intend to pay *

09:16.288 --> 09:18.725
* The elves are
back to work today *

09:18.826 --> 09:21.828
Hooray!

09:21.928 --> 09:25.999
* We have just a couple hours to
make several billion gifts *

09:26.099 --> 09:28.301
* And the labor
isn't easy *

09:28.400 --> 09:30.570
* Then you'll all work
triple shifts *

09:30.671 --> 09:32.905
* You can make the job
go quicker *

09:33.005 --> 09:36.976
* If you turn up the controls
to superspeed *

09:37.076 --> 09:40.648
[ Tempo Quickens ] * It's back
to work on Xmas Eve *
[ Panting ] Hooray.

09:40.748 --> 09:44.417
* And though you're cold
and sore and ugly *

09:44.517 --> 09:47.654
* Your pride
will mask the pain *

09:47.754 --> 09:51.158
* Let my happy smile
warm your heart *

09:51.258 --> 09:54.360
* There's a toy
lodged in my brain *

09:54.461 --> 09:57.965
* We are getting awfully tired
and we can't work any faster *

09:58.065 --> 10:01.634
* And we're very, very sorry
* Why, you selfish
little bastards *

10:01.735 --> 10:05.806
* Do you want the kids
to think that Santa's just
a crummy, empty-handed jerk *

10:05.905 --> 10:09.677
- Ow!
- * Then shut your yaps
and back to work *

10:12.011 --> 10:14.214
* Now it's
very nearly Xmas *

10:14.313 --> 10:16.950
* We've done the best we could
* These toy soldiers
are poorly painted *

10:17.049 --> 10:18.951
* And they're made
from inferior wood *

10:19.052 --> 10:22.522
* I should give you all
a beating, but I really
have to fly *

10:22.621 --> 10:25.958
* If I weren't stuck here
frozen, I'd harpoon you
in the eye *

10:26.058 --> 10:29.663
* Now it's back
into our tenements
to drown ourselves in rye *

10:29.763 --> 10:33.734
* You did the best you could
I guess, and some of
these gorillas are okay *

10:33.834 --> 10:35.335
Hooray!
We're adequate!

10:35.434 --> 10:38.672
* The elves have rescued
Xmas Day **
Hooray!

10:44.177 --> 10:46.078
Giddyap.

10:55.688 --> 10:58.859
Duh, gee, Bender,
how're you gonna get
through these bars?

10:58.959 --> 11:01.695
I don't know, moron.
Suppose I bend 'em?

11:01.794 --> 11:04.030
Duh, okay.

11:04.130 --> 11:06.332
Ow!
Mommy! Mommy!

11:06.432 --> 11:09.168
- Santa's through the perimeter!
- This is it, kids!

11:09.269 --> 11:11.671
Take your suicide pills
so you won't suffer!

11:11.772 --> 11:14.006
No! Wait!
I'm the good Santa.

11:14.106 --> 11:17.043
I've got toys,
at very reasonable prices.

11:17.144 --> 11:20.913
Don't listen to him.
He's the father of all lies
and the uncle of all tricks.

11:21.014 --> 11:23.250
But I come bearing
Tri-Ominos.

11:23.350 --> 11:27.888
- Go for the shins!
- Aah! Ow, ow, ow, ow! Ow!

11:30.957 --> 11:34.394
[ Groans ]
One down.

11:39.631 --> 11:43.302
[ Gasps ]
Well, hello there, handsome.

11:43.403 --> 11:45.538
Won't you have a... cookie?

11:45.638 --> 11:48.942
Ah, don't mind if I do.
Heh!

11:49.042 --> 11:50.977
Ow! What's in these things?

11:51.077 --> 11:54.914
Why don't you slip
into something more fiery?

11:55.014 --> 11:58.284
Ow! Oh! Yah!

11:58.384 --> 12:00.620
Ow! Aah!

12:00.720 --> 12:04.591
[ Yells, Grunts ]
Ow.

12:07.995 --> 12:10.629
Yo, Kringle!
What happened to you, dawg?

12:10.730 --> 12:14.100
Oh, it's awful, Kwanzabot.
Everyone hates me.

12:14.201 --> 12:17.004
[ Scoffs ]
At least they understand you.
You know what I'm saying?

12:17.104 --> 12:19.005
Ain't nobody down
with this Kwanza tip.

12:19.105 --> 12:21.942
Hey, maybe you can lend me
a hand with these deliveries?

12:22.042 --> 12:26.245
[ Imitates Buzzer ]
No time. I got to hand out
the traditional Kwanza book.

12:27.815 --> 12:32.284
[ Sighs ]
I've been giving these out
for 647 years.

12:39.625 --> 12:41.693
[ Growls ]

12:41.794 --> 12:43.831
Ah, bathtub eggnog.

12:43.931 --> 12:46.665
Just the way
Grandma used to drink.

12:46.765 --> 12:49.937
[ Slurps ]
Eww! It went sour!

12:50.037 --> 12:53.005
Can't I have
a scented bath in peace?

12:53.105 --> 12:56.209
Remember, Professor,
Bender is Santa.

12:56.308 --> 12:59.346
So we don't need
to hurt him, right?
Yes, yes, yes!

12:59.446 --> 13:01.714
You sound like
a broken MP3.

13:01.815 --> 13:04.817
Ho, ho-- Ow!

13:04.918 --> 13:08.020
Professor! Don't you
remember what I told you?

13:08.120 --> 13:10.023
No!

13:10.123 --> 13:12.125
[ Groans ]

13:14.126 --> 13:17.898
Oh, there's gotta be
a better way.

13:22.501 --> 13:26.306
Bender, you're a genius.
[ Sinister Laughter ]

13:26.405 --> 13:30.543
This creates an unrealistic
standard of beauty.
[ Snorts ]

13:30.643 --> 13:34.313
Now it's time for Santa
to screw open his present.

13:37.384 --> 13:39.852
It's Santa,
and we got him cornered.

13:39.952 --> 13:42.355
Oh, I smell
a juicy promotion for me.

13:42.455 --> 13:45.024
And a juicy rehiring back
onto the force for me.

13:45.125 --> 13:47.427
Hey, wh-- what?

13:53.732 --> 13:56.937
This Xmas Day session of court
will come to order.

13:57.037 --> 13:59.505
The Honorable
Judge Whitey presiding.

14:01.008 --> 14:04.677
Santa Claus, you stand accused
of crimes against humanity.

14:04.777 --> 14:06.678
How do you plead?

14:06.778 --> 14:09.015
Not Santa.
There he is again!

14:09.115 --> 14:11.018
[ Whimpers ]

14:11.118 --> 14:15.923
Now, Pramala, I know it's scary
in that there witness box,

14:16.023 --> 14:18.857
but 'tain't no need
to fear me.

14:18.958 --> 14:20.860
[ Clucks Loudly ]
Aah!

14:20.961 --> 14:23.395
I'm sorry.
I thought you was corn.

14:23.495 --> 14:28.201
Now, would you please point
at that robot over there?

14:28.301 --> 14:30.102
[ Spectators Murmuring ]

14:30.202 --> 14:32.404
No further questions.

14:34.706 --> 14:37.809
[ Peeping ]
Daddy done good, huh?

14:37.911 --> 14:41.914
Isn't it true that
you have been paid
for your testimony?

14:42.014 --> 14:44.716
Yes. You gave me a dollar
and some candy.

14:44.817 --> 14:47.419
And yet you haven't said
what I told you to say.

14:47.519 --> 14:49.489
How can any of us
trust you?

14:51.724 --> 14:53.725
Quit badgering the witness.

14:53.826 --> 14:56.663
Badger? Where?
[ Clucking ]

14:57.830 --> 15:00.667
Whereas I have a ham dinner
with mayonnaise...

15:00.767 --> 15:02.970
waiting for me
at my mansion,

15:03.070 --> 15:05.004
I find the defendant guilty.

15:05.105 --> 15:09.176
- [ All Gasp ]
- Santa Claus,
I hereby sentence you...

15:09.275 --> 15:12.178
to be executed
at sundown.

15:12.278 --> 15:14.846
- Oh!
- It's not fair.

15:14.947 --> 15:17.985
I just hope that dumb chicken
is ashamed of himself.

15:18.085 --> 15:21.421
[ Crowing ]

15:26.359 --> 15:29.162
Deactivated robot walking!

15:29.261 --> 15:32.099
We got a deactivated
robot walking here.

15:32.198 --> 15:34.866
[ Whirring ]

15:34.967 --> 15:39.005
Hey, Santa, when you
see the robot devil,
tell him I'm a-comin'.

15:40.706 --> 15:43.842
Hey, that guy said
to tell you that--
I heard him.

15:50.517 --> 15:52.884
** [ "Pop Goes The Weasel" ]

15:52.985 --> 15:55.154
Greetings, masters!

15:55.254 --> 15:58.158
My companion and I
made lots of toys.

15:58.258 --> 16:00.192
Out of my way, shrimpo.

16:00.293 --> 16:02.562
We're here to bring
Santa back so we can prove
Bender's innocence.

16:02.662 --> 16:05.298
[ Buzzing ]

16:06.966 --> 16:11.171
Do what you will,
but we'll see
who has the last "ho."

16:11.270 --> 16:15.008
[ All Grunting ]
There.

16:15.107 --> 16:17.009
Oh, no!
The ice is melting!

16:17.110 --> 16:20.647
The pollution from the factory--
it caused a greenhouse effect.

16:20.746 --> 16:23.816
- That would explain this heat.
- And your breezy short shorts.

16:23.916 --> 16:26.253
Uh, yeah, that
would explain it.

16:26.352 --> 16:28.687
[ Roars ]

16:28.788 --> 16:30.590
[ All Screaming ]

16:36.995 --> 16:39.331
[ All Screaming ]

16:40.567 --> 16:43.669
[ Machinery Humming ]

16:43.769 --> 16:45.904
[ Panting ]

16:46.004 --> 16:48.575
[ Muttering, Grunting ]

16:48.674 --> 16:50.842
[ Grunting ]

16:52.845 --> 16:55.347
[ Santa Grunts ]
Oh!

17:01.221 --> 17:04.757
Hurry! We've gotta think
of another way to save Bender,
or Xmas will be ruined.

17:04.856 --> 17:07.026
Especially for Bender.

17:10.962 --> 17:12.898
Look out, Earth.

17:12.999 --> 17:16.635
I'm dreaming
of a red Xmas.

17:16.736 --> 17:20.307
[ Evil Laughter ]

17:25.211 --> 17:29.148
Ah, good old Maggie.
Huh? Eh.

17:29.249 --> 17:33.051
When I pull the switch,
these powerful electromagnets
will tear you limb from limb,

17:33.153 --> 17:35.555
killing you in the most
humane possible manner.

17:35.654 --> 17:38.790
But, Mr. Mayor,
that doesn't sound humane!

17:38.891 --> 17:41.827
It is for the witnesses
because it's not boring.

17:45.832 --> 17:50.502
The instant this random
number generator reaches zero,
you'll be executed.

17:50.603 --> 17:53.740
- [ Groans ]
- Ten.

17:53.839 --> 17:56.008
Three.

17:56.108 --> 17:58.244
Twelve. Three again.

17:58.345 --> 18:00.980
- Stop the execution!
- Leela!

18:01.079 --> 18:05.417
- Fifteen. Negative eight.
- You've got the wrong Santa,
and I'll prove it.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.920
I'm Santa Claus.
[ Gasping ]

18:08.019 --> 18:11.523
- What? Twenty-seven.
- No, I'm Santa Claus.

18:11.624 --> 18:14.527
- Six?
- [ Low-pitched Voice ]
We're also Santa Claus.

18:14.626 --> 18:16.695
And I'm his friend Jesus.

18:16.796 --> 18:20.833
Your Mayorness,
if you execute him,
you have to execute all of us.

18:20.932 --> 18:24.136
You people aren't Santa.
You're not even robots.

18:24.237 --> 18:28.039
Ninety-one.
How dare you lie
in front of Jesus.

18:28.141 --> 18:30.210
Hey, zero.

18:30.309 --> 18:32.345
[ Electronic Humming ]

18:32.444 --> 18:34.046
No! Stop the magnet!

18:34.146 --> 18:36.816
[ Voice Quavering ]
* Swing low

18:36.915 --> 18:40.153
* Sweet chariot

18:40.252 --> 18:43.522
* Comin' for
to carry me home *

18:43.623 --> 18:45.892
- * Swing low *
- This is horrible.

18:45.991 --> 18:47.993
But it's not boring.

18:49.229 --> 18:52.030
Ho, ho, ho!

18:53.900 --> 18:55.867
Oh!

18:55.968 --> 18:57.869
[ All Screaming ]

18:57.970 --> 19:00.539
My God, the real Santa!
Get him, Jesus!

19:00.640 --> 19:03.675
I help those
who help themselves!
[ Whimpering ]

19:05.211 --> 19:08.347
Santa! You saved my life.
Please don't kill me.

19:08.448 --> 19:12.652
Ha, ha, ho, ho, ho!
I'm not here
to kill you, Bender.

19:12.751 --> 19:15.887
I need you to help me
save Xmas.

19:17.690 --> 19:19.759
Gee whiz, Santa.

19:19.858 --> 19:22.060
You want me to help you?

19:22.161 --> 19:26.199
- Don't do it! He's evil!
- I know he is,
but I have no choice.

19:26.298 --> 19:30.436
I'm running late,
and if I don't complete
my brutal rampage,

19:30.537 --> 19:33.272
well, it just
wouldn't be Xmas.

19:33.373 --> 19:35.275
I guess what
I'm asking is,

19:35.375 --> 19:39.546
Bender, won't you join
my slaying tonight?

19:39.645 --> 19:42.281
Well, 'tis the season.

19:59.365 --> 20:02.034
[ All Screaming ]

20:02.134 --> 20:04.604
Aah!

20:04.703 --> 20:07.473
My hair!
My wedding cake!

20:07.574 --> 20:10.410
[ Laughing ]
Let it snow!

20:12.412 --> 20:15.448
Merry Xmas, kids.
[ Grunts ]

20:15.548 --> 20:17.784
[ Grunting ]

20:17.884 --> 20:20.287
Aah!

20:20.386 --> 20:22.989
[ Laughing ]

20:25.657 --> 20:27.426
This wangs chung.

20:27.527 --> 20:30.997
After all the good we tried
to do, Xmas turned out
as rotten as ever.

20:31.096 --> 20:33.098
No heat.
No power.

20:33.199 --> 20:37.103
Huddled together in fear,
like lice in a burning wig.

20:37.202 --> 20:41.007
Wait a second.
Maybe your futuristic Xmas
isn't so rotten, after all.

20:41.106 --> 20:44.611
What are you talking
about, you crouton?
You said it yourself.

20:44.711 --> 20:48.448
Xmas should be about
bringing people together,
not blowing them apart.

20:48.548 --> 20:51.417
But don't you see?
Fear has brought us together.

20:51.518 --> 20:53.420
That's the magic of Xmas.

20:53.519 --> 20:56.323
That's a big crock of--

20:56.423 --> 20:58.525
Hold me.

21:05.498 --> 21:09.501
On, Trasher!
On, Smasher!

21:09.602 --> 21:12.605
- Hey, Kwanzabot.
Where are you off to?
- You didn't hear about it?

21:12.704 --> 21:16.008
Chanukah Zombie's having
a luau at the B'nai B'rith.
You comin'?

21:16.107 --> 21:18.678
Word.

21:18.778 --> 21:22.348
By the way, Bender,
here's a small token
of my appreciation...

21:22.449 --> 21:25.217
for being Santa while
I was trapped in the ice.

21:25.317 --> 21:27.819
Oooh!
[ Chuckling ]

21:27.920 --> 21:30.656
Hey, chief, you screwed up.
There's nothing in here.

21:30.757 --> 21:34.560
Oh, it might appear empty,
but the message is clear.

21:34.661 --> 21:36.663
Play Santa again,

21:36.762 --> 21:39.865
and I'll kill you next year.

21:39.965 --> 21:43.970
Aah!

21:45.070 --> 21:50.809
Ho, ho, ho!
